mpionships and one Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 634, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world's most-decorated track and field athletes\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 568}, {\"ngram\": \"Gong\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"two world championships\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 606}, {\"ngram\": \"one Olympic gold medal\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 633}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She threw 20.58 meters to establish her personal best and take home the gold from the pandemic-delayed Tokyo Olympics in 2021.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 761, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 738, \"end\": 752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999997116902, \"rank\": 2.882235127008815e-10, \"text\": \"Tokyo Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"20.58 meters\", \"from\": 645, \"to\": 657}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold\", \"from\": 703, \"to\": 711}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before that glorious moment, she finished in third, second and fourth place in the previous three editions of the Games in Beijing, London and Rio de Janeiro, respectivley.\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 934, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 885, \"end\": 892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9966435989866771, \"rank\": 0.0033677043796922885, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 894, \"end\": 900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9884145982221845, \"rank\": 0.01172090021379369, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 905, \"end\": 919, \"title\":